[49m[38;5;10m+      1[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Recipe 9.1: Python Implementation Example
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      2[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Heads up:** This is a deliberately simple, illustrative implementation of the pseudocode walkthrough from Recipe 9.1. It shows one way you could translate those concepts into working Python code. It is not production-ready. There's no DICOM parsing from a real modality, no trained model weights, and the "ML inference" is simulated. Think of it as the sketchpad version: useful for understanding the shape of the solution, not something you'd deploy to a radiology department on Monday morning. Consider it a starting point, not a destination.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      6[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Setup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll need the AWS SDK for Python and a few image processing libraries:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3 numpy
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m For real DICOM parsing you'd also want `pydicom` and for production image processing `opencv-python`, but this example uses numpy directly to keep dependencies minimal and demonstrate the core concepts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs credentials configured (via environment variables, an instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs `sagemaker:InvokeEndpoint`, `s3:GetObject`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, and `sns:Publish`.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Config and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Before we get to the steps, here's the configuration that drives the quality assessment decisions. Thresholds live at the top of your module because they're the first thing you'll tune per deployment site. (You will tune them. Every imaging department has different equipment, different standards, and different tolerance for false positives.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # QUALITY_THRESHOLDS: per-modality decision boundaries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Each modality/body_part combination gets its own thresholds because
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # what counts as "acceptable" varies wildly. A chest X-ray needs to be
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # sharp enough to see interstitial markings. A bone density scan has
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # completely different requirements.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # "accept": images scoring above this pass automatically.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # "review": images between "review" and "accept" get flagged for tech review.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Below "review": immediate reject, retake recommended.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # These numbers are starting points. Calibrate them against your
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # radiologists' actual rejection patterns during a shadow-mode period.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m QUALITY_THRESHOLDS = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "CR_CHEST": {"accept": 0.85, "review": 0.65},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "CR_EXTREMITY": {"accept": 0.80, "review": 0.60},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "CT_HEAD": {"accept": 0.90, "review": 0.70},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "CT_ABDOMEN": {"accept": 0.85, "review": 0.65},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "MR_KNEE": {"accept": 0.80, "review": 0.60},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "MR_BRAIN": {"accept": 0.90, "review": 0.70},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "DEFAULT": {"accept": 0.85, "review": 0.65},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # BLUR_THRESHOLD: minimum Laplacian variance for an image to be considered sharp.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Below this, the image is definitely blurry regardless of what the ML model says.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # This is the "fast reject" gate for obvious motion blur.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Typical range: 100-500 depending on modality and image resolution.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BLUR_THRESHOLD = 100.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # DYNAMIC_RANGE_MINIMUM: minimum difference between 5th and 95th percentile
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # pixel values. Below this, the image is essentially blank or saturated.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m DYNAMIC_RANGE_MINIMUM = 50
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # SAGEMAKER_ENDPOINT_NAME: the deployed model endpoint for ML-based assessment.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     61[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # This model was trained on your institution's historical PACS rejection data.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     62[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SAGEMAKER_ENDPOINT_NAME = "image-quality-model"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     63[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     64[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # SNS_TOPIC_ARN: where quality failure alerts go.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SNS_TOPIC_ARN = "arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:123456789012:quality-alerts"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # DYNAMODB_TABLE: where assessment results are stored.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m DYNAMODB_TABLE = "quality-assessments"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     70[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     71[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     72[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     73[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: Receive and Parse the Image
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     74[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
